## Prerequisites

- **Node.js** 18+
- A **Firebase project** ([console.firebase.google.com](https://console.firebase.google.com/))
- A **Google Cloud Console** account (linked automatically to your Firebase project)
- Package manager: `npm` (default), `pnpm`, `yarn`, or `bun`

## Quick Start

```bash
# 1. Install dependencies
npm install

# 2. Copy env template and fill in values (see "Environment Variables" below)
cp .env.example .env.local

# 3. Run dev server
npm run dev
```

Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) and visit `/login`.

