## Auth Flow

| Route | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `/register` | Create account (email/password<!-- IF oauth=google --> or Google<!-- /IF -->) → session cookie set → redirect to `/dashboard` |
| `/login` | Sign in (email/password<!-- IF oauth=google --> or Google<!-- /IF -->) → session cookie set → redirect to `/dashboard` |
| `/forgot-password` | Triggers Firebase password reset email |
| `/reset-password` | Completes reset (token from email) |
| `/dashboard` | Protected — requires valid `__session` cookie |

Behavior is enforced by:

- `src/middleware.ts` — fast cookie existence check (Edge Runtime)
- `src/app/(protected)/layout.tsx` — cryptographic session verification on the server (`adminAuth.verifySessionCookie()`)

Middleware **only checks cookie existence** (Edge can't run Firebase Admin SDK). Real verification happens in the protected layout.

